               <history>
                  <origin>
                     <origDate notBefore="1500" notAfter="1800">16th-18th century,
                                                        </origDate>
                  </origin>
                  <provenance>Note of ownership by Mammerē (f. 1a) and by Bēta Giyorgis (f. 24a). The [Argānona dengel] is purchased by Anāneyos (f. 129a) a name that substituted the erased name of the original owner (f. 39a). Śarsa Ab is the name substituted in the [Ta'ammera Māryām] (ff. 145a and 147a).  In Institute of Ethiopian studies when filmed.</provenance>
               </history>
